<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-08-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-08-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Signor
                                    <persName type="to">Carignani</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-08-12"><hi rend="italic">August 12,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 700.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 30th ultimo, giving certain information
                            obtained by the Italian consular authorities relating to the killing of
                            two Italians and the wounding of a third at Erwin, Miss.</p>
                        <p>This information has been communicated to the governor of
                            Mississippi.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>